<br>
&quot;Farewell Mother.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=lacacora>LaCa Cora</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#993300>(12/18/00 7:56:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Cora's Goodbyes</span><hr size=1>  Cora stood next to her mother.  Tears were bliked back as a few different emotions ran through her.  She had really never taken the time to truly get to know her grandmother, and she the remorse was great. Kneeling and bowing her head, Cora prayed silently to the Gods that Sayler was well in Hades Domain, and that they would someday meet and she would finally know her grandmothers unconditional love. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/umegdream.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Meg Dream</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#993300>(12/18/00 7:58:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sayler Renee Loire's Memorial</span><hr size=1> Even though Sayler wasn't her daughter anymore, she still loved her as one, she approached the Memorial, and placed a hand on Aly's shoulder. She sighed, and took a deep breath.<br>
<br>
&quot;When someone dies, they aren't really gone, Aly. We have to keep their memory alive in our hearts. Sayler wouldn't want us grieving for her...but...be happy for her because she's in a better place.&quot;<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uarahutajiwarli.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arahuta Jiwarli</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.hometown.aol.com/arahutajiwarli/star-14.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Shamaness</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#993300>(12/19/00 5:03:58 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Memorial</span><hr size=1> :::Not knowing this amazon, Ara stood at the top of the hill gazing down upon the amazons.  She softly chanted the ancient death song her mother had taught her many years ago.  The song sang of a life lived in honor and greatness, and of joining the spirits who bless the earth.  And that the one who left rejoins us who stayed.::: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uhippolyte.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hippolyte</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://hometown.aol.com/queenhippolyte/spinningsword.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Vasilissa</span><br>  Posts: 168<br> <font color=#993300>(12/19/00 6:17:13 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/pleiade3/ehipp.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Memorial</span><hr size=1> :::Hipp walked up the hill, and stopped beside Arahuta.  She smiled softly listening to the soft voice that sang some foreign language that she heard from time to time from the dark warrior.  She then looked down at the amazons assembled.  She had only heard of Sayler and not knowing her.  But, she felt that she should pay her respects.  She nodded to Arahuta, and then walked down to join the others. Hippolyte placed a small silver labrys near the other objects laid down.  The labrys being the long adopted symbol of the amazons.  Hippolyte saluted Sayler and then stepped back to allow the immediate family their time.  She quietly walked up and rejoined Ara at the top of the hill, gave her a respectful smile.  And then went home.  <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>
