<br>
&quot;Rest well, athelfi.&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=tiger4157>Tiger4157</A> at: 12/20/00 1:34:59 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rishkaeamzn>RishkaeAmzn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon </span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#993300>(12/20/00 12:31:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Memorial</span><hr size=1> Rishkae walked to the memorial, holding a black length of cloth in her hand. Aly's mother she had never known, but she showed respect for both. Bowing, she whispered:: <br>
<br>
&quot;May the afterlife be kind to your soul Athelfi&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ucallistowarriorqueen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CallistoWarriorQueen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#993300>(12/21/00 5:13:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Memorial</span><hr size=1> Not won to show emotion, she looked at the others, all saluting the dead one, she stood there, in silence, not saying a word, the wind blowing her long blonde hair violently. She watched as the others payed tribute to her, and she stood on the hill top, paying her silent respects. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uxvgabriellebard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>XvGabrielleBard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon Bard</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#993300>(12/21/00 5:37:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Memorial</span><hr size=1> Gabrielle approached the memorial silently to pay her respects. She laid several flowers down then bowed her. She had never met Sayler, but she knew she had to be a wonderful woman and mighty Amazon to raise Alysia, and her other children, on her own so well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showMessage?topicID=63.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showMessage?topicID=58.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.emailTo